Information
------------------------------

Secret Life Of The Human Pups
Documentary shedding light on people living extraordinary double lives as `human pups', dressing up in elaborate dog suits and engaging in `human puppy play', which sees them devouring dog treats, indulging in belly rubs, and frolicking with squeaky toys. This unusual subculture has become a global phenomenon in recent years, with an estimated 10,000 `human pups' living in the UK alone, and this film sets out to determine the movement's appeal. The programme also explores the wider repercussions of this odd way of life, including the impact living as a dog has on a person's friends and family.
